The PUSH( ) operation is used to add an 
element to the top of the stack.
It follows the LIFO (Last-In, First-Out) rule, 
which means the element added last will be 
removed first.
PUSH( ) is a basic and important operation in a stack. 
When you use PUSH, the new element is placed on 
the top position of the stack.
When we try to insert (PUSH) an element into a 
stack that is already full, it is called Stack 
Overflow.
PUSH( ) OPERATION
