POP( ) OPERATION
POP( ) operation is used to remove an element 
from the stack. The element is always removed 
from the top of the stack because stack follows 
the LIFO (Last-In-First-Out) principle. 
Before removing, the stack is checked to see if it 
is empty. If the stack is empty, it shows "STACK 
UNDERFLOW". Otherwise, the top element is 
removed and the value of top is decreased by 
one. It is one of the basic operations performed 
in a stack.
