• Used to delete or remove an element or an item
from top of the stack
• Removing an element from stack called
pop operation
• A series of steps involved in pop operation
• Step 1 – checks if the stack is empty.
• Step 2 – if the stack is empty, produces an error and exit.
• Step 3 – if the stack is not empty, accesses 
the data element at which top is pointing.
• Step 4 – decreases the value of top by 1.
• Step 5 – returns success.
POP operation
