Stack UNDERFLOW
Stack underflow in
Stack:-
ALGORITHM:-
►Stack Underflow occurs when we 
try to remove (POP) an element from 
a stack that is already empty.
►A stack becomes empty when the 
value of top = −1. If we try to POP an 
element, there is no element 
available, so STACK UNDERFLOW 
occurs.
