Implementation of Stack using Array
•When we perform PUSH, the top increases 
and the element is added.
•When we perform POP, the top element is 
removed and top decreases.
•The size is fixed, so if the array becomes full, 
it causes Stack Overflow.
•This method is simple, fast, and easy to 
implement.
•Array stack behaves like a fixed-size 
container.
In array implementation, stack elements are stored in a fixed-size 
array. A variable called top is used to track the last inserted element.
Engineer dude learning
Engineer dude learning
Enginee
Engin
Engin
Engin

Implementation of Stack using Linked lists
•When we perform PUSH, a new node is created 
and added at the top.
•When we perform POP, the top node is removed 
and top moves to the next node.
•The size is not fixed, so the stack can grow 
dynamically.
•This method is memory efficient and flexible.
•Linked list stack behaves like a chain that can grow 
endlessly, limited only by system memory.
In linked list implementation, stack elements are stored in nodes 
connected by links. The top points to the first node.
