Evaluating Arithmetic Expression using Stack
An  arithmetic expression is a combination of operands
(A, B, X, Y) and operators (+, −, ×, ÷) used to perform calculations.
In computer science, stack is used to evaluate arithmetic 
expressions.
Example:  A + B
Notations-
Infix, Postfix and Prefix notations are three different but equivalent 
ways of writing expressions.
Engineer dude learning
Engineer dude learning
Enginee
