Engin
Engin

2.Prefix expression (Polish notation):
Operator is before operands.
An expression is called the prefix expression.  if the operator appears before the 
operands. Simply of the form (operator operand1 operand2).
Example: +AB
3) Postfix expression (Reverse Polish notation):
Operator is after operands. 
An expression is called the postfix expression if the operator appears after the 
operands. Simply of the form (operand1 operand2 operator).
Example: AB+
1) Infix expression:
Operator is between operands. 
An expression is called the infix expression if the operator appears 
between the operands. Simply of the form (operand1 operator operand2).
Example: A+B
