1.Limited access
You can access only the top element, not middle or bottom.
2. Fixed size problem (in array stack)
Stack overflow occurs if stack becomes full.
3. Memory wastage
If stack is not fully used, memory remains unused.
4. Stack overflow risk
Too many elements or recursive calls can crash program.
5. Not suitable for all applications
If random access is needed, stack is not useful.
Disadvantages of Stack
