• Queue is based on FIFO (First-in-First-out) principle.
• Unlike stacks, a queue is open at both it ends.
• Two operations are performed
• Enqueue or insertion – insert an element
• Dequeue or deletion – delete an element
• To maintain queue two pointers are used
• Front
• Rear
Introduction to Queue
• It is an abstract data type (ADT)
data structure like stack.
