• Adding an object to a queue is called
"insertion or enqueue". 
• It is always added at the end of the queue,
which is called the "rear."
• Removing an object from a queue is called 
"deletion or dequeue".
• It is always removed from the front of the 
• queue, which is called the "front.“
• Real life Example:-
Queue
