Operations in Queue
1. Enqueue (Insertion):
Adds an element at the rear (end) of the queue.
2. Dequeue (Deletion):
Removes an element from the front of the queue.
3. Peek (Front):Shows the front element without 
removing it.
4. Rear: Get the last item from queue.
5. isEmpty(): Checks whether the queue is empty or not.
6. isFull(): Checks whether the queue is full or not.
Time Complexity: Queue Time complexity of all operations like enqueue(), 
dequeue(), isFull(), isEmpty(), front() and rear() is O(1). There is no loop in any 
of the operations. 
