1. Simple Queue (Linear Queue): Insertion at 
rear and deletion from front.
2. Circular Queue: Last position connects to first, 
forming a circle.
3. Priority Queue: Elements are removed based 
on priority, not order.
4. Deque (Double Ended Queue): Insertion and 
deletion allowed at both ends.
Types of Queue
